WEBVTT

00:00.102 --> 00:01.851
Previously on <i>The Client List</i>
You met someone?

00:01.972 --> 00:03.562
I'm Harold.
It's a pleasure.

00:03.682 --> 00:05.701
Selena: Your client Lisa has been
in here multiple times a week.

00:05.821 --> 00:07.210
I left my husband.
Let's talk about us.

00:07.244 --> 00:08.467
We work together

00:08.587 --> 00:10.950
It's just a little naughty fun on the side,
no strings attached.

00:11.070 --> 00:12.763
You think that I'm a thief.
I quit.

00:12.883 --> 00:13.716
Riley: Nikki...
She's in trouble.

00:13.750 --> 00:15.934
- She's working over at wild nights.
Selena: - That guy's no good.

00:16.053 --> 00:17.338
What makes you think
Carlyle's gonna listen to you?

00:17.458 --> 00:18.554
Because
he's driven by money.

00:18.589 --> 00:19.895
Is there something going on with
you and my brother?

00:20.015 --> 00:20.621
I don't know.

00:20.741 --> 00:21.891
You never did have the balls
to go out

00:22.011 --> 00:23.226
and make a life of your own,
did you?

00:23.260 --> 00:24.994
We absolutely
cannot do this anymore.

00:25.028 --> 00:27.763
You're under arrest. I had
no idea you were so strong.

00:27.797 --> 00:29.064
There's a lot about me
you don't know.

00:29.099 --> 00:30.633
Prosecutors want
Kyle's accomplice.

00:30.667 --> 00:32.634
I had a choice to make.
I chose you.

00:32.668 --> 00:33.936
What do you want?

00:33.970 --> 00:36.040
I'll pay you $50,000
to sleep with you.

00:36.160 --> 00:36.958
Are you okay?

00:37.078 --> 00:38.026
I just need Riley
to get here.

00:38.146 --> 00:39.734
[ Laughter ]
Riley, I need you here.

00:39.854 --> 00:41.753
- Where the heck are you?
- You missed this for work?

00:41.873 --> 00:43.711
I'm always there for you,
whatever you need.

00:43.831 --> 00:46.230
- I need you to understand.
- I think I understand just fine.

00:46.350 --> 00:48.317
[ Sizzling ]

00:48.352 --> 00:50.353
[ Birds chirping ]

00:55.125 --> 00:57.693
Kyle?

00:57.727 --> 00:59.328
You're out?

00:59.363 --> 01:01.330
You did it, baby.

01:01.365 --> 01:02.731
You got me out.

01:04.968 --> 01:06.802
You're beautiful.

01:06.836 --> 01:08.538
[ Chuckles ]

01:14.178 --> 01:15.478
Beautiful slut.

01:15.512 --> 01:17.480
[ Gasps ]

01:17.514 --> 01:20.316
[ Sighs ]

01:33.129 --> 01:34.496
- Mommy?
- Oh.

01:34.530 --> 01:36.131
[ Clears throat ]
Hey, baby.

01:36.166 --> 01:38.767
The daddy-daughter dance
is tomorrow,

01:38.802 --> 01:40.635
but daddy isn't home.

01:40.670 --> 01:42.137
Oh, he will be.

01:42.172 --> 01:44.339
Soon?

01:44.373 --> 01:46.175
Yeah, um...
You know what?

01:46.209 --> 01:48.110
When your daddy was away
playing football,

01:48.144 --> 01:49.744
your Uncle Evan,
he took me to prom

01:49.779 --> 01:51.246
so I wouldn't
have to go alone.

01:51.281 --> 01:52.614
- He did?
- Mm-hmm.

01:52.648 --> 01:53.982
Pretty good dancer, too.

01:54.017 --> 01:55.517
Better than daddy?

01:55.551 --> 01:57.019
Well,
maybe just a little.

01:57.053 --> 01:58.854
Do you think
he'll take me?

01:58.888 --> 02:00.622
You're just gonna
have to ask him, won't you?

02:00.656 --> 02:02.657
We girls
have to do everything.

02:02.692 --> 02:04.126
I know, right?

02:04.160 --> 02:05.928
[ Laughing ] Come here.

02:05.962 --> 02:08.330
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, I love you.

02:08.364 --> 02:10.699
[ Smooching ]

02:10.818 --> 02:13.493
<font color="#3399FF">The Client List 02x08</font>
<font color=#00ff00>Heaven's Just A Sin Away</font>
Original Air Date April 28, 2013

02:13.613 --> 02:15.447
==sync, correction by <font color=#00ff00>dcdah</font>==
for www.addic7ed.com

02:15.805 --> 02:18.606
Mornin'.

02:18.641 --> 02:20.608
I told Taylor I would
handle Linette's clients

02:20.643 --> 02:22.010
while she's in rehab.

02:22.045 --> 02:23.478
She said her appointment book
was here.

02:25.581 --> 02:27.049
I'm in a rush.

02:27.083 --> 02:29.117
I've got a bridal party
coming to the salon.

02:29.152 --> 02:31.320
Okay.
So we're doing this.

02:31.354 --> 02:32.721
Is she okay?

02:32.755 --> 02:34.556
She's fine.
You know mama.

02:34.590 --> 02:36.658
She can bend,
but she won't break.

02:36.692 --> 02:38.493
Well...

02:38.527 --> 02:39.794
Look, Lacey.

02:39.829 --> 02:41.897
I am punishing myself
as it is, okay?

02:41.931 --> 02:44.799
So the cold-shoulder thing,
it really isn't necessary.

02:44.834 --> 02:48.203
Well, sometimes, I'm too good
at holding a grudge.

02:48.238 --> 02:50.038
- Did you handle your sitch?
- Huh?

02:50.073 --> 02:52.307
You said you missed
Earlene's shower

02:52.342 --> 02:53.708
'cause you had
a situation at work?

02:53.743 --> 02:56.544
Oh, yeah. Um...
It was an electrical thing.

02:56.579 --> 02:59.314
Anyway,
thanks for helping mom.

02:59.349 --> 03:01.216
Of course. Got to run.

03:01.251 --> 03:04.052
[ Door opens ]
Hey.

03:04.087 --> 03:05.420
I just got
a message from Katie.

03:05.454 --> 03:06.688
I was on my way
to the academy.

03:06.722 --> 03:08.590
- Everything okay?
- She called you?

03:08.624 --> 03:10.259
I am so sorry.

03:10.293 --> 03:11.894
It is nothing that you needed
to come over here for.

03:11.928 --> 03:15.330
Katie!
Your Uncle Evan is here.

03:15.365 --> 03:16.731
Uncle Evan,
can you take me

03:16.766 --> 03:19.902
to the daddy-daughter dance
tomorrow?

03:20.937 --> 03:23.772
You know what?

03:23.806 --> 03:26.375
There's nothing
I'd rather do.

03:26.409 --> 03:27.842
And I have a feeling

03:27.877 --> 03:29.244
you're gonna be
the most beautiful one there.

03:35.751 --> 03:38.921
You believe I just celebrated
my 10-year anniversary?

03:38.955 --> 03:40.588
10 years?
Wow, that is a long time.

03:40.623 --> 03:43.792
My wife insists we do
traditional anniversary gifts.

03:43.826 --> 03:45.294
You know what 10 years is?

03:45.328 --> 03:46.528
Mnh-mnh.

03:46.562 --> 03:47.629
Tin.

03:47.663 --> 03:49.264
Tin.

03:49.299 --> 03:51.900
Well, that...
That is a tough one.

03:51.935 --> 03:55.103
No. Three words...
Tin beverage tub.

03:55.138 --> 03:57.439
I'll fill that bad boy with ice,
some beers,

03:57.473 --> 03:58.506
and call it a day.

03:59.775 --> 04:01.743
Now,
can we do the good stuff?

04:01.777 --> 04:02.811
[ Sighs ]

04:05.982 --> 04:09.651
I'm suddenly feeling
a little feverish.

04:09.685 --> 04:12.387
Now we're talking, dirty mama.
No, no, no.

04:12.422 --> 04:14.990
No, like, um... like a "flu
coming on" kind of feverish,

04:15.024 --> 04:17.225
so I'm just gonna have
one of the other girls

04:17.260 --> 04:18.593
finish your massage

04:18.627 --> 04:20.829
'cause I-I wouldn't
want you to get sick.

04:24.968 --> 04:27.769
I'm gonna need you
to take over my massage.

04:27.803 --> 04:29.771
Oh, sorry. No can do.

04:29.805 --> 04:31.606
Why? He a little too
freaky-deaky?

04:31.640 --> 04:33.108
No. Not at all.

04:33.142 --> 04:34.476
I just feel like
I'm coming down with something.

04:34.510 --> 04:35.910
Hmm. I heard there's a nasty bug
going around.

04:35.945 --> 04:37.512
Oh, see? Nasty bug.
And I'm getting it.

04:37.546 --> 04:39.747
[ Coughs ]

04:39.782 --> 04:41.149
Can you take over
my massage?

04:41.184 --> 04:42.451
Sure. I got him.

04:42.485 --> 04:44.453
[ Sighs ] Thank you.
Oh, and remember,

04:44.487 --> 04:47.655
it's "Starve a fever,
feed a cold."

04:47.690 --> 04:49.858
Or is it "Feed a fever,
starve a cold"?

04:49.892 --> 04:52.694
You should rest.

04:52.728 --> 04:54.696
There's a walk-in
for a deep-tissue massage

04:54.730 --> 04:56.431
if anybody's got time.

04:56.466 --> 04:58.833
Mnh-mnh. Not it.
Yeah, I'll take it.

04:58.868 --> 05:00.469
I'll take it, even though
I really do... [ coughs ]

05:00.503 --> 05:02.304
I'm really starting
to fight something.

05:02.338 --> 05:03.472
I'll let him know.

05:03.506 --> 05:05.307
[ Door closes ]

05:05.341 --> 05:09.277
Oh, I get it.
You're atoning.

05:09.312 --> 05:12.680
12 years of catholic school.
Should have kept that uniform.

05:12.715 --> 05:16.518
I am just a massage therapist
trying to give a legit massage.

05:16.552 --> 05:18.720
Plain and simple.
Mm-hmm.

05:18.754 --> 05:20.455
You know, when I was babysitting
the other night,

05:20.490 --> 05:23.458
you came home looking
upset as a sinner in a cyclone.

05:23.493 --> 05:26.294
It was Dylan, wasn't it?

05:26.329 --> 05:29.297
Come on. Tell me.
Come on. How much he pay you?

05:29.332 --> 05:32.300
I bet you made
a truckload.

05:32.335 --> 05:35.504
Look,
the guilt goes away.

05:35.538 --> 05:36.638
You know,
I'm not feeling like

05:36.672 --> 05:39.041
an Oprah moment right now,
so...

05:39.075 --> 05:40.675
Look, I was just
trying to help, you know.

05:40.709 --> 05:42.577
You need somebody
to talk to...

05:42.611 --> 05:44.979
Yeah, well,
I'll bring it up.

05:45.014 --> 05:46.548
Well, okay, fine.

05:50.119 --> 05:52.521
What's this?

05:52.555 --> 05:54.556
I'm ordering
more glasses for the bar,

05:54.590 --> 05:56.191
and you have
the best taste.

05:56.225 --> 05:58.826
- Oh. This one.
- Mmm.

05:58.861 --> 06:01.663
I like that you know
when to let me decide.

06:01.697 --> 06:04.266
Well, I like that you know
what you want.

06:04.300 --> 06:05.600
[ Both laugh ]

06:05.634 --> 06:06.868
Oh, Riley. Hey.

06:06.902 --> 06:09.104
Hey. Sorry.
Am I slowing your roll?

06:09.138 --> 06:11.106
Only temporarily.

06:11.140 --> 06:13.241
I'm gonna go order
these glasses.

06:13.276 --> 06:15.677
All that loving
make a girl jealous.

06:15.711 --> 06:18.447
- What's up, honey?
- I am having a rough day.

06:18.481 --> 06:20.549
- Want to talk about it?
- Well, let's see... I am married,

06:20.583 --> 06:21.950
and I slept with a man
for money,

06:21.984 --> 06:22.951
so there's always that.

06:22.985 --> 06:24.286
I crossed a line

06:24.320 --> 06:25.753
that you told me
that I shouldn't cross.

06:25.788 --> 06:28.190
And is it bad for me to drink
during the day?

06:28.224 --> 06:30.058
Oh, not today.

06:30.093 --> 06:32.927
- Whiskey.
- Whiskey. All right, then.

06:32.962 --> 06:34.296
[ Sighs ]

06:34.330 --> 06:35.897
The guilt is just
eating me alive inside.

06:35.931 --> 06:38.100
I can relate to that.

06:38.134 --> 06:40.268
Hey, why don't you
come to church Sunday?

06:40.303 --> 06:43.138
Uh, that is so not what
I thought you were gonna say.

06:43.172 --> 06:44.772
Come on, Riley. I'm serious.
This is the only place

06:44.807 --> 06:46.774
that will lift me up
when no one else can.

06:46.809 --> 06:48.143
You know
I met Harold there.

06:48.177 --> 06:49.978
Yeah, I don't think
that church and I

06:50.012 --> 06:51.613
are gonna be getting along
right now.

06:51.647 --> 06:54.449
Okay. Harold, honey,
come over here

06:54.484 --> 06:56.818
and tell Riley about
Southern Hope Baptist.

06:56.852 --> 06:58.653
I'm trying to convince her
to go to church Sunday.

06:58.687 --> 07:00.655
Oh, that place
always lifts me up.

07:00.689 --> 07:02.157
You know,
that's where I met Georgia.

07:02.191 --> 07:03.558
Oh, God,
please tell me you two

07:03.593 --> 07:05.093
are not gonna start
dressing alike.

07:05.128 --> 07:07.095
No, no. We wouldn't steer you
wrong. You should come.

07:07.130 --> 07:09.431
I mean, the...
The choir's gonna be amazing,

07:09.465 --> 07:11.466
- and the coffee ain't bad, either.
- Oh, that coffee is terrible.

07:11.501 --> 07:12.767
So bad.

07:12.801 --> 07:14.169
Oh, yeah,
don't drink the coffee.

07:14.203 --> 07:17.405
- No.
- Okay, well, I'm in.

07:17.440 --> 07:19.407
Whoa.
[ Glass thuds ]

07:19.442 --> 07:22.010
Hey, Jeanne.
It's Lacey from the salon.

07:22.044 --> 07:24.012
I just wanted to let you know
that something came up

07:24.046 --> 07:26.648
and Linette isn't available
for your appointment,

07:26.682 --> 07:29.651
but I'd be happy
to do it for you.

07:29.685 --> 07:32.086
Yep. Same time.
Okay. See you then.

07:32.121 --> 07:33.755
[ Cellphone beeps ]

07:33.789 --> 07:36.758
Hey, uh, would you mind turning
up that dryer in 10 minutes?

07:36.792 --> 07:38.860
I got to go rinse Ms. Coleman
before she ends up

07:38.894 --> 07:40.462
looking like strawberry shortcake.
Of course.

07:40.496 --> 07:42.497
Bless your heart for
helping Linette out in this way.

07:42.532 --> 07:44.132
You're a good person.

07:44.167 --> 07:46.768
Well, I'm doing what I can.
She's been like a mama to me.

07:46.802 --> 07:50.505
Well, I'm sure it takes
a load off Riley, too.

07:50.540 --> 07:52.374
Can't say I'm not
a little envious of you two.

07:52.408 --> 07:54.476
Y'all are closer than
me and my sister will ever be.

07:54.510 --> 07:56.378
Don't ever let anything
get in the way of that.

07:56.412 --> 07:59.047
[ Telephone rings ]
Oh. Hello. Curl Up & Dry.

08:04.019 --> 08:05.187
[ Door closes ]

08:05.221 --> 08:06.221
Riley?

08:06.255 --> 08:09.090
Laundry room!

08:14.730 --> 08:16.498
So, I'm gonna enter
my Grandpa Orval's pickles

08:16.532 --> 08:18.166
into the "Taste of Texas"
contest.

08:18.201 --> 08:21.570
Uh, I told you that I'm already
sorry enough for both of us.

08:21.604 --> 08:23.338
You don't have to make me
eat those in the morning.

08:27.376 --> 08:29.744
Mmm. It's good.

08:29.778 --> 08:33.215
Good? These things
are better than good.

08:33.249 --> 08:34.849
They're salty, garlicky,
crunchy Spears of heaven.

08:34.883 --> 08:37.686
Mm-hmm, mm,
speaking of heaven,

08:37.720 --> 08:39.721
you want to go
to church with me?

08:39.755 --> 08:41.155
I'm kind of maxed out

08:41.190 --> 08:43.991
from Linette dragging us there
every Sunday.

08:44.025 --> 08:46.094
Oh, um...

08:48.130 --> 08:51.132
I'm really sorry
that I let you down.

08:52.968 --> 08:55.237
Oh, my God.

08:55.271 --> 08:58.607
These are Hakari
Jaguar Scissors.

09:00.109 --> 09:02.677
Okay.

09:02.712 --> 09:03.911
Church, scissors.

09:03.946 --> 09:06.281
What are you keeping
from me?

09:06.315 --> 09:07.849
- Nothing.
- Really?

09:07.883 --> 09:10.017
Remember when you shaved
Ken and Barbie's heads?

09:10.052 --> 09:11.419
You were so scared
to tell me

09:11.454 --> 09:12.721
that you bought me
the Barbie dream pool?

09:12.755 --> 09:15.123
I didn't make it
to the shower

09:15.157 --> 09:16.524
'cause I was with a man.

09:16.559 --> 09:19.361
You had a date
and you didn't tell me?

09:19.395 --> 09:20.395
What about Kyle?

09:20.429 --> 09:21.996
No, it wasn't a date.

09:23.232 --> 09:29.571
One of my clients paid me
$50,000 to sleep with him.

09:31.407 --> 09:33.375
And you can be mad at me

09:33.409 --> 09:35.209
or yell at me now
or something, anything.

09:35.244 --> 09:36.811
Just don't...

09:36.845 --> 09:39.447
Ohh, don't do
that deep-freeze thing.

09:44.820 --> 09:46.788
Oh, well, I just...

09:46.822 --> 09:48.790
I might just need a minute
to wrap my mind around this.

09:48.824 --> 09:50.992
I mean, I... I'm s-sitting here,
telling you about

09:51.026 --> 09:52.294
my Grandpa Orval's pickles,

09:52.328 --> 09:54.596
and you...
you tell me that you...

09:54.630 --> 09:56.665
you had sex for $50,000?

09:56.699 --> 09:58.667
[ Sighs ]

09:58.701 --> 10:00.835
I mean, this is exactly
what I was worried about

10:00.869 --> 10:04.472
when you started doing...
whatever it is you're doing.

10:04.507 --> 10:05.674
You know what, Lacey?

10:05.708 --> 10:08.910
I... I've really needed
the money.

10:08.944 --> 10:12.146
And it's just
a one-time thing, so...

10:12.181 --> 10:15.183
Please don't look at me
like that.

10:15.217 --> 10:16.918
I told you I feel bad,
okay?

10:16.952 --> 10:18.186
But when
you look at me like that,

10:18.220 --> 10:20.622
it...
just makes me feel like

10:20.656 --> 10:22.791
I am the worst
person in the world.

10:22.825 --> 10:25.794
I am not judging you.

10:25.828 --> 10:27.962
I'm just
worried about you.

10:27.996 --> 10:29.964
[ Doorbell rings ]

10:29.998 --> 10:31.899
Excuse me.

10:37.673 --> 10:38.840
Kyle.

10:38.874 --> 10:40.942
Hi.
Lacey: On second thought,

10:40.976 --> 10:44.111
I think
we could use us some church.

10:48.750 --> 10:50.769
I-I'm sorry for
just stopping by.

10:50.889 --> 10:52.334
I wanted to surprise
the kids.

10:52.368 --> 10:55.136
I didn't know that you were
being released so soon.

10:55.170 --> 10:56.804
I should have called.

10:56.839 --> 11:00.642
I'm gonna go make sure the kids
are ready for Sunday School.

11:00.676 --> 11:02.143
So, um,
we're just heading out.

11:02.177 --> 11:03.345
Sure, yeah.

11:03.379 --> 11:05.347
Yeah, you...
You can come, if you want.

11:05.381 --> 11:07.982
Or I could just, you know,
call you when we get back.

11:08.016 --> 11:09.351
Where you gonna be?

11:09.385 --> 11:10.685
I got to meet
with the lawyer.

11:10.720 --> 11:11.986
Okay.

11:12.888 --> 11:15.323
- Daddy!
- Daddy!

11:15.358 --> 11:16.491
Oh, I missed you!

11:16.525 --> 11:20.595
Oh, I missed you two
so much.

11:20.630 --> 11:23.265
Mama, can we stay home
with daddy?

11:23.299 --> 11:26.668
Uh...
He has a meeting, so...

11:26.702 --> 11:28.603
- You're not gonna leave us again, are you?
- Oh, no. No.

11:28.638 --> 11:31.539
I'm never leaving you
ever again.

11:31.574 --> 11:33.341
Pinky swear?

11:33.376 --> 11:34.776
Pinky swear.

11:34.810 --> 11:36.210
[ Smooches ]

11:36.245 --> 11:38.045
[ Sighs ]

11:38.080 --> 11:41.215
Come on, guys.
It's time to go. Okay.

11:43.819 --> 11:45.153
[ Clears throat ]

11:45.187 --> 11:47.155
I can call you when, uh...
when we get back

11:47.189 --> 11:50.358
so that you can
spend some time with them.

11:52.395 --> 11:53.361
Pinky swear?

11:53.396 --> 11:55.096
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

12:00.403 --> 12:02.203
[ Whistle blows ]

12:02.237 --> 12:05.239
This is your final
tactical simulation!

12:05.274 --> 12:07.475
It is pass or fail!

12:07.510 --> 12:10.144
We have a hostage-rescue
scenario!

12:10.179 --> 12:13.147
And I don't need anybody
looking stupid on my watch!

12:13.182 --> 12:15.550
Hey, Shelby. You free
for dinner tomorrow night?

12:15.584 --> 12:17.552
You're asking me
on a date now

12:17.586 --> 12:19.754
right before
our last tactical?

12:19.789 --> 12:21.389
Yeah, I am.

12:21.424 --> 12:22.824
Thought you'd never ask.

12:22.858 --> 12:24.426
Bad Jack's.
Pick you up at 8:00.

12:24.460 --> 12:25.827
Ugh.

12:25.861 --> 12:27.495
What? You got something
against barbecue?

12:27.530 --> 12:29.864
- I'm a vegetarian.
- You serious?

12:29.898 --> 12:32.467
Hope you're not that gullible
during the hostage rescue.

12:33.902 --> 12:36.404
[ Bell tolling ]

12:36.439 --> 12:37.706
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:37.740 --> 12:41.376
Lacey,
that guy's from the list.

12:43.813 --> 12:47.181
So is he.

12:47.216 --> 12:48.717
Harold, hey.

12:48.751 --> 12:50.585
- Hey, Riley. I'm happy you made it.
- Hi.

12:50.619 --> 12:52.387
- We sold you on that coffee, didn't we?
- Yes. [ Laughs ]

12:52.421 --> 12:55.423
Come on. Let me introduce you
to Pastor Duncan.

12:55.458 --> 12:56.758
- Pastor D.
- Hey.

12:56.792 --> 12:58.693
Hey, man.
Meet my girls Riley and Lacey.

12:58.813 --> 12:59.446
Hi.

12:59.566 --> 13:01.763
Harold: These ladies
are friends of Georgia's.

13:01.797 --> 13:03.598
Oh, okay.
It's nice to have you.

13:03.632 --> 13:05.266
It's always good
to see new faces.

13:05.300 --> 13:06.901
Yeah, so, Riley here
just took over The Rub.

13:06.935 --> 13:08.102
Is that right?

13:08.136 --> 13:09.537
Yeah, I did. Mm-hmm.

13:09.572 --> 13:11.573
Harold:
And I owe her everything.

13:11.607 --> 13:14.275
Because of her, I get to spend
more time with my lady.

13:14.309 --> 13:15.810
Okay, well,
I'll have to stop by.

13:15.845 --> 13:17.412
I've got a bum shoulder
that could use some work.

13:17.446 --> 13:20.415
Someone fouls too hard
in our basketball league,

13:20.449 --> 13:22.984
but it wouldn't be Christian
to call him out by name.

13:23.018 --> 13:24.819
[ Chuckles ]
You know what?

13:24.854 --> 13:26.821
It was a pleasure to meet you.
And, uh, we should get a seat.

13:26.856 --> 13:27.822
- Yeah?
- Okay.

13:27.857 --> 13:29.591
- Enjoy.
- See you, guys.

13:29.625 --> 13:31.893
- Take care of that bum shoulder.
- Okay. [ Chuckles ]

13:31.927 --> 13:33.762
Good morning,
good morning.

13:35.765 --> 13:40.735
♪ Lift up your hands ♪

13:40.770 --> 13:43.137
♪ your voice ♪

13:43.171 --> 13:45.139
♪ let's rejoice ♪

13:45.173 --> 13:47.609
♪ in love ♪

13:47.643 --> 13:51.078
♪ your hands, your voice ♪

13:51.113 --> 13:52.814
I guess I should just
put my scissors in there.

13:52.848 --> 13:54.649
No,
do not give the big guy

13:54.683 --> 13:56.785
anything sharp
he can use against me.

13:56.819 --> 13:58.953
If I were you,
I'd pay up.

13:58.987 --> 14:01.923
Hey, I'm not the one who's
trying to get square with God.

14:01.957 --> 14:05.460
[ Applause ]

14:08.997 --> 14:12.366
I just celebrated
20 years of marriage.

14:12.401 --> 14:14.068
[ Applause ]

14:20.476 --> 14:25.279
Now, people say
I must feel lucky, blessed...

14:25.314 --> 14:28.616
Man: - Say it!
- Like I have accomplished something.

14:28.651 --> 14:30.017
All right, now.

14:30.052 --> 14:34.021
And, yes,
I feel all those things,

14:34.056 --> 14:39.226
but marriage is a commitment,
not a feeling.

14:39.261 --> 14:40.695
Marriage is work.
[ Chuckles ]

14:40.729 --> 14:42.697
[ Crowd murmurs ]

14:42.731 --> 14:46.133
Marriage
is honor and honesty.

14:46.168 --> 14:47.669
Is he talking to me?

14:47.703 --> 14:49.136
He's looking right at me.

14:49.171 --> 14:50.505
Well,
he can probably see

14:50.539 --> 14:52.707
that broken halo
hanging off your head.

14:52.741 --> 14:55.643
Marriage
is appreciating your partner,

14:55.678 --> 14:57.479
treating them with respect.

14:57.513 --> 14:59.180
Be kind to your husbands.

14:59.214 --> 15:00.815
Is it hot in here?

15:00.850 --> 15:04.018
Do your best
to lift each other up.

15:04.052 --> 15:06.253
Adulteress.

15:06.288 --> 15:07.689
Adulteress!

15:07.723 --> 15:08.823
Adulteress!

15:08.858 --> 15:10.424
[ Gasps ]

15:10.459 --> 15:13.194
Riley, what are you doing?
[ Breathing heavily ]

15:13.314 --> 15:14.340
And I'd like to acknowledge...

15:14.460 --> 15:15.371
I'm gonna get some fresh air.

15:15.491 --> 15:18.933
our visiting pastors. All the way from
Des Moines, Iowa, Pastor Thomas.

15:18.968 --> 15:21.068
[ Applause ]

15:22.538 --> 15:24.038
And Pastor Williams,
gracing us

15:24.072 --> 15:26.173
with his presence
from Tallahassee, Florida.

15:26.208 --> 15:28.810
[ Applause ]

15:30.613 --> 15:32.780
You've agreed to testify,
and you know that your immunity

15:32.815 --> 15:34.782
is contingent
on your testimony.

15:34.817 --> 15:37.218
All right, now's the time
to be squeaky clean.

15:37.252 --> 15:39.053
Can't be around
any convicted felons.

15:39.087 --> 15:40.421
Can't even jaywalk.

15:40.455 --> 15:42.423
- Understood.
- And get a job.

15:42.457 --> 15:45.426
Look, I get it. I want to
provide for my family.

15:45.460 --> 15:47.395
This is your
witness prep.

15:47.429 --> 15:49.397
Now, you have
little credibility,

15:49.431 --> 15:51.232
and Vandermeyer's lawyers
know it.

15:51.266 --> 15:52.767
They're gonna
try to slice you up.

15:52.801 --> 15:55.403
Let's run through a few of these
and see where we are.

15:55.437 --> 15:58.072
Is it true
that you left your family?

16:00.442 --> 16:01.976
Answer the question,
Mr. Parks.

16:02.011 --> 16:03.778
You left your wife and children
to buy drugs in Mexico.

16:03.812 --> 16:05.112
Yes or no?

16:05.147 --> 16:07.081
Look, I don't understand
what any of this

16:07.115 --> 16:08.449
has to do with Vandermeyer.

16:08.483 --> 16:10.284
I saw him make
false insurance claims.

16:10.318 --> 16:12.119
I mean, the guy bribed
a congressman.

16:12.154 --> 16:13.555
He's guilty.

16:13.589 --> 16:15.423
- Answer the question.
- Look... do you mind

16:15.457 --> 16:18.860
if I just go over these
on my own first?

16:20.663 --> 16:23.064
Just to be clear,

16:23.098 --> 16:24.666
this is the most important
thing you can do

16:24.700 --> 16:26.901
for you and your family.

16:26.936 --> 16:30.104
Get it right.

16:32.056 --> 16:34.475
Harold. Hi.

16:34.509 --> 16:37.612
Hey.
Everything okay?

16:37.646 --> 16:39.113
[ Sighs ]

16:39.147 --> 16:42.784
To be honest, I don't think
that I belong here.

16:42.818 --> 16:45.186
I guarantee

16:45.220 --> 16:48.189
the folks in this building
have felt that way before.

16:48.223 --> 16:50.625
I mean,
I was a musician on the road,

16:50.659 --> 16:52.827
so I've done
my share of sinning.

16:52.861 --> 16:54.528
Does Georgia know?

16:54.563 --> 16:56.764
Like the back of her hand.
That's the good thing about us.

16:56.799 --> 16:58.232
We don't
have any secrets.

17:00.002 --> 17:01.368
I know
it's not my business,

17:01.403 --> 17:03.004
but if something
is bothering you...

17:03.038 --> 17:06.440
Uh, it's just the...
sermon.

17:06.474 --> 17:08.442
It hit
pretty close to home.

17:08.477 --> 17:10.277
I'm having some trouble
in my marriage.

17:10.311 --> 17:12.680
And I shouldn't
be talking to you about this.

17:12.714 --> 17:14.381
Not to pry,

17:14.415 --> 17:18.019
but have you and your husband
tried talking to someone?

17:18.053 --> 17:19.453
You mean
like counseling?

17:19.488 --> 17:21.689
- Yeah.
- No, we've never been.

17:21.723 --> 17:24.626
If you're open to it,

17:24.660 --> 17:26.828
they offer it
here at the church.

17:26.862 --> 17:29.664
Might be good
to talk through things.

17:29.698 --> 17:33.300
Yeah, a lot of damage
has been done.

17:33.335 --> 17:34.702
I'm not sure
this is the kind of thing

17:34.737 --> 17:37.538
that gets better
by talking about it.

17:37.572 --> 17:39.306
Yeah.

17:39.341 --> 17:41.509
Well, it might be
a good place to start.

17:41.543 --> 17:42.910
[ Chuckles ]
Maybe.

17:42.945 --> 17:45.913
You're a good man,
Harold.

17:45.948 --> 17:48.215
[ Chuckles ]

17:48.250 --> 17:49.717
Come on.

17:49.752 --> 17:52.820
You're not gonna want to miss
the testimonials.

17:52.855 --> 17:54.421
People say
the damnedest things.

17:54.456 --> 17:56.090
[ Laughs ]
It's very entertaining.

17:59.762 --> 18:01.562
Okay.

18:01.596 --> 18:03.998
[ Chuckles ]

18:04.033 --> 18:07.334
All right.
Now, you know what time it is.

18:07.369 --> 18:11.338
[ Crowd murmurs ] 'Cause if the spirit
moves you, then please, stand up.

18:11.373 --> 18:12.740
Testify.

18:12.775 --> 18:15.176
[ Man coughs ]

18:15.210 --> 18:18.546
Okay, um, Brother Harold.

18:18.580 --> 18:20.581
[ Piano playing ]

18:25.554 --> 18:28.522
Uh, one of the...
The best days of my life

18:28.557 --> 18:32.126
was when I-I found the...
The good man upstairs...

18:32.161 --> 18:33.227
Man: Testify.

18:33.261 --> 18:35.730
And stopped acting a fool.

18:35.764 --> 18:37.398
[ Laughter ]

18:37.432 --> 18:42.570
And the next best day
was when I found Georgia.

18:42.604 --> 18:44.605
[ Crowd murmurs ]

18:46.508 --> 18:48.475
You, uh...

18:48.510 --> 18:50.011
You make me a better man.

18:54.616 --> 18:56.884
[ Crowd gasping ]

18:56.919 --> 18:58.953
Come on back, honey.
Excuse me.

18:58.987 --> 19:00.554
[ Laughter ]

19:00.589 --> 19:03.091
Georgia Cummings...

19:04.159 --> 19:06.060
will you marry me?

19:06.095 --> 19:07.829
Yes.

19:07.863 --> 19:10.664
[ Chuckles ]
Yes, yes, yes!

19:10.699 --> 19:11.766
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:11.800 --> 19:13.968
Yes! Oh, yes!

19:14.002 --> 19:16.503
Yes, yes!
[ Laughs ]

19:16.538 --> 19:19.741
Move away, right?

19:19.775 --> 19:23.277
I have a little testimonial
of my own.

19:23.311 --> 19:25.913
♪ At last ♪

19:25.948 --> 19:28.950
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:28.984 --> 19:32.186
♪ My love has come along ♪

19:32.221 --> 19:34.655
[ Piano plays ]

19:36.458 --> 19:40.261
♪ My lonely days are over ♪

19:40.295 --> 19:43.164
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:43.198 --> 19:47.601
♪ And life, it's like a song ♪

19:47.636 --> 19:50.772
♪ song ♪

19:50.806 --> 19:52.907
Hey!

19:52.941 --> 19:54.308
♪ I found a dream ♪

19:54.342 --> 19:56.310
♪ found a dream ♪

19:56.344 --> 19:59.213
♪ that I can speak to ♪

19:59.248 --> 20:05.052
♪ - ooh, ooh, ohh, ah ♪
♪ - a dream that I can call my own ♪

20:05.087 --> 20:06.387
♪ call my own ♪

20:06.421 --> 20:09.390
Woman: - Sing!
♪ - I found a thrill ♪

20:09.424 --> 20:14.228
♪ - ooh, ooh ♪
♪ - to press my cheek to ♪

20:14.263 --> 20:20.434
♪ - ah, ah, yeah, yeah ♪
♪-  a thrill that I have never known ♪

20:20.468 --> 20:21.836
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:21.870 --> 20:24.638
[ Singing continues
in distance ]

20:40.759 --> 20:43.194
I'm sorry. Did you need
more time to undress?

20:45.364 --> 20:47.365
[ Chuckles ]

20:49.734 --> 20:51.702
Just a little something
to thank you

20:51.736 --> 20:55.339
for motivating me to leave that
God-awful marriage I was in.

20:58.911 --> 21:02.313
Lisa, I...
I can't accept this.

21:02.347 --> 21:03.514
Please.

21:03.548 --> 21:05.917
Divorce is making me
a rich woman.

21:05.951 --> 21:09.186
And a single one.
[ Chuckles ]

21:10.789 --> 21:14.992
Now, is there any chance
you could unzip me?

21:15.027 --> 21:19.063
I ache all over.

21:22.267 --> 21:26.237
Yeah.

21:26.271 --> 21:28.672
Hey.

21:28.706 --> 21:30.507
Hey.
Thanks for calling.

21:30.542 --> 21:32.509
Yeah, the kids have been
dying to see you.

21:32.544 --> 21:35.512
Um... how did it go
with the attorney?

21:35.547 --> 21:37.915
Are we safe, I mean, with you
testifying and everything?

21:37.950 --> 21:39.750
- Yeah, we're safe.
- Okay.

21:39.784 --> 21:41.585
I just would be lying
if I didn't say

21:41.619 --> 21:44.588
that this whole Vandermeyer
thing makes me very nervous.

21:44.622 --> 21:47.591
Look, I-I get that, but you
heard what Graham said, right?

21:47.625 --> 21:49.260
The police
are watching him,

21:49.294 --> 21:51.228
and he'd be a fool to come
after us, and he knows it.

21:51.263 --> 21:53.464
Everything's
gonna be okay.

21:53.498 --> 21:58.135
Hey. Nothing to
be scared of, okay?

21:59.938 --> 22:04.308
Um... we're gonna eat.
Do you want to stay?

22:04.343 --> 22:07.311
Yeah.
That'd be really nice.

22:07.346 --> 22:09.546
Daddy! Come see the pictures
we drew for you!

22:09.581 --> 22:11.382
We drew you a picture
at Sunday School!

22:11.416 --> 22:12.583
You did?

22:12.617 --> 22:13.784
[ Riley chuckles ]

22:13.818 --> 22:16.253
How sweet!

22:20.492 --> 22:22.460
Hey.
Hi.

22:22.494 --> 22:24.295
[ Door closes ]

22:24.329 --> 22:28.065
So, uh,
saw Lisa on the books.

22:28.100 --> 22:29.467
Thought you cut her off.

22:29.501 --> 22:30.901
Eh.
Hmm.

22:30.935 --> 22:32.503
Why don't you look at
that fancy watch of yours

22:32.537 --> 22:35.172
and tell me what time it is?
Oh, wait. I know.

22:35.207 --> 22:37.174
It's seven minutes past
what the hell are you thinking

22:37.209 --> 22:39.076
accepting gifts
from crazy-ass clients?

22:39.111 --> 22:40.911
She caught me off guard.

22:40.945 --> 22:44.615
I want to keep her around.
She pays well.

22:44.649 --> 22:47.251
She is
one glass of wine away

22:47.285 --> 22:49.186
from tying you up in the attic
and boiling your bunny.

22:49.221 --> 22:50.621
[ Chuckles ]

22:50.655 --> 22:54.025
Look, taking that watch
is just a bad idea.

22:54.059 --> 22:56.160
Why? Mr. Louboutin
buys you shoes.

22:56.194 --> 22:57.694
What's the difference?

22:57.729 --> 22:59.296
Okay, first of all,
Mr. Louboutin

22:59.331 --> 23:01.332
is not trying to
make me his wife.

23:01.366 --> 23:03.534
And that's no Faux-Lex.
What are you doing to her?

23:03.568 --> 23:05.602
Just the usual.

23:05.637 --> 23:06.970
Oh, the usual?

23:07.005 --> 23:08.050
Mm-hmm.

23:08.170 --> 23:11.108
Like what?
Um, like we do, usual?

23:11.228 --> 23:13.877
Mnh-mnh. What we do
is better than usual.

23:15.047 --> 23:17.014
[ Gasps ]
Wait. Are you...

23:17.049 --> 23:18.149
Am I what?

23:18.183 --> 23:20.317
You're jealous.
[ Laughs ]

23:20.352 --> 23:21.663
Please.

23:21.783 --> 23:24.438
- She's just a client.
- Fine. Fine. Crazy.

23:24.558 --> 23:26.823
And I mean
she's bat-shit crazy.

23:26.858 --> 23:28.225
[ Laughing ] But whatever
you want to do.

23:28.260 --> 23:30.027
She can't do this,
though.

23:32.864 --> 23:35.866
[ Sighs ]

23:39.605 --> 23:40.757
Katie: <i>This one looks like you.</i>
Kyle: <i>Which one?</i>

23:40.877 --> 23:41.654
Kyle: <i>Are you crazy?
That does not look like me.</i>

23:41.774 --> 23:43.174
- Yeah, it does.
- That does not look like me.

23:43.208 --> 23:45.577
You look like a girl.
You look like a grandma.

23:45.611 --> 23:48.412
It's like
I've spotted bigfoot.

23:48.447 --> 23:49.847
Yeah, it's strange,
isn't it?

23:49.882 --> 23:52.050
My babies look happy,
though.

23:52.084 --> 23:53.851
- Okay, he does.
- Don't... come on. Don't cheat. Come on.

23:53.886 --> 23:55.853
[ Giggling ]

23:55.888 --> 23:58.690
So, is he... I mean,
is this, like, you know,

23:58.724 --> 24:00.658
Riley and Kyle,
business as usual?

24:00.693 --> 24:03.527
You want to remind me
what that looks like?

24:03.562 --> 24:06.230
Oh, my God.
I forgot about the dance.

24:06.264 --> 24:08.733
Hey, Katie,
your Uncle Evan is here.

24:13.438 --> 24:15.673
Welcome home.

24:15.708 --> 24:18.576
Thanks. You didn't have to get
all dressed up on me.

24:18.611 --> 24:20.612
Okay, so here's the deal.
Um...

24:20.646 --> 24:23.014
Evan was just gonna take Katie
to the daddy-daughter dance

24:23.048 --> 24:24.849
because I didn't know
that you were gonna be home.

24:24.883 --> 24:26.584
You know, Katie,
maybe you want your daddy

24:26.619 --> 24:28.586
to take you to the dance.

24:28.621 --> 24:29.921
Katie: But mommy says
if you tell someone

24:29.955 --> 24:31.422
you're gonna do something,
you do it.

24:31.456 --> 24:32.790
Well, I did say that.

24:32.825 --> 24:35.426
No, Katie's right.

24:35.460 --> 24:36.761
It's the right thing
to do.

24:39.331 --> 24:41.799
You have a good time with your Uncle Evan
tonight, okay? But now that I'm back,

24:41.834 --> 24:44.502
I'm gonna be your date
next time, okay?

24:45.398 --> 24:48.106
And mommy says
Uncle Evan dances better than...

24:48.140 --> 24:51.776
Oh. [ Laughs ] Katie.
[ Chuckles ] Kids.

24:51.810 --> 24:54.779
Why don't you go get on your dress
and get ready? I'll go help her.

24:54.813 --> 24:56.614
Hey, dad,
let's play some catch.

24:56.649 --> 24:59.283
Yeah,
let's do it, buddy.

25:07.760 --> 25:11.963
Thank you for taking her.
It really means a lot.

25:14.767 --> 25:16.734
[ Sighs ]

25:16.769 --> 25:20.337
You really think
a man lives up there?

25:20.372 --> 25:23.574
[ Laughs ]
I don't know.

25:23.608 --> 25:25.409
You know
what I remember?

25:25.443 --> 25:27.244
I remember reading
"Goodnight Moon"

25:27.279 --> 25:30.081
to you and your little sister,
and you guys giggling

25:30.115 --> 25:32.283
about cows
jumping over the moon.

25:32.317 --> 25:34.018
Mom,
that book's for babies.

25:34.053 --> 25:37.955
I'm so sorry. You know what?
You will always be my baby.

25:37.990 --> 25:40.158
[ Smooches ]

25:40.192 --> 25:42.593
I still don't think
cows jump over the moon.

25:42.627 --> 25:44.996
Yeah, well,
you're probably right.

25:45.030 --> 25:46.430
Did I just hear
you two say

25:46.464 --> 25:48.099
that a cow can't jump
over the moon?

25:48.133 --> 25:49.600
Yeah.

25:49.634 --> 25:50.835
You ever see a shooting star?
Mm-hmm.

25:50.869 --> 25:52.469
Yeah, well,
I hear a shooting star

25:52.504 --> 25:54.305
is Big Bessie making her
way through space.

25:54.339 --> 25:55.506
[ Giggles ]

25:55.540 --> 25:57.809
I'm... I'm serious.
[ Laughs ]

25:57.843 --> 25:59.811
Okay, why don't you
go get ready for bed?

25:59.845 --> 26:02.046
Kiss your daddy,
and I'll be in in a minute.

26:08.053 --> 26:11.956
[ Sighs ]
You're still wearing it.

26:11.990 --> 26:13.290
We're still married.

26:13.325 --> 26:15.026
I know.

26:15.060 --> 26:19.630
Kids are so happy
that you're here.

26:19.664 --> 26:21.065
This is complicated.

26:21.100 --> 26:23.735
I know.

26:23.769 --> 26:26.137
I'm gonna earn my way
back into the house.

26:26.171 --> 26:27.538
Where you gonna stay?

26:27.572 --> 26:30.374
I don't know.
I'll figure it out.

26:30.408 --> 26:33.010
You want to sit with me
for a while?

26:33.045 --> 26:35.012
Yeah.
I could do that.

26:35.047 --> 26:39.416
♪ Let's say
you change your ways ♪

26:39.451 --> 26:42.854
♪ Let's say you admit mistakes ♪

26:42.888 --> 26:46.858
♪ you should have known better ♪

26:46.892 --> 26:50.527
♪ but I've heard that before ♪

26:51.797 --> 26:55.767
[ Knock on door ] ♪ It's what
happens when you don't show ♪

26:55.801 --> 27:00.071
♪ It's what happens when
you don't call ♪

27:00.105 --> 27:06.710
♪ It's what happens
when you don't know me at all. ♪

27:09.815 --> 27:13.617
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

27:13.652 --> 27:17.855
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

27:17.890 --> 27:24.095
♪ What happens
when you don't know me at all ♪

27:25.969 --> 27:27.757
[ Drawer slams ]

27:29.067 --> 27:30.868
You staying here
is temporary, right?

27:30.903 --> 27:33.237
Yeah, it is.

27:33.272 --> 27:36.107
And so is you
being a father to my kids.

27:36.141 --> 27:40.544
We're blood,
so I'm helping you out.

27:40.578 --> 27:43.948
But just so we're clear,
we're not friends.

27:43.982 --> 27:46.217
I will never
respect you again.

27:46.251 --> 27:47.819
Yeah.

27:47.853 --> 27:49.220
That's rich
coming from the man

27:49.254 --> 27:50.988
who tried to steal
his brother's wife.

27:57.095 --> 27:58.984
[ Door closes ]

28:01.240 --> 28:04.023
I'm sick of carrots.
I'm gonna turn orange.

28:04.143 --> 28:06.244
Yes, you are gonna turn orange,
and you're gonna like it.

28:06.279 --> 28:08.480
- They're good for your eyes.
- So are cookies.

28:08.514 --> 28:11.349
No. Go and get your backpacks.
We're gonna be late.

28:13.850 --> 28:14.727
Daddy!

28:14.847 --> 28:15.763
Dad!

28:15.921 --> 28:17.922
Okay, kids, go, go, go!
Straight to the car!

28:17.956 --> 28:21.439
Come on! Sorry.
We're just running behind.

28:21.559 --> 28:22.926
I mean, I can
take them to school.

28:22.961 --> 28:24.561
No, it's okay.
We have a routine.

28:24.595 --> 28:25.963
And I need to talk to
one of Travis' teachers,

28:25.997 --> 28:27.364
and we have this song
that we listen to

28:27.398 --> 28:28.565
right as we
get out of the car.

28:28.599 --> 28:30.233
But do you
let Evan take them?

28:30.268 --> 28:32.435
Please don't go there,
okay?

28:32.470 --> 28:35.238
I have enough on my plate
with mom in rehab and...

28:35.273 --> 28:36.740
What?
Linette's in rehab?

28:36.775 --> 28:38.308
You missed a lot, Kyle.

28:39.341 --> 28:42.079
Look, we'll figure out
how to do this, okay?

28:42.113 --> 28:43.480
And what is this?

28:43.514 --> 28:46.316
I made us an appointment
for counseling,

28:46.350 --> 28:50.453
so we'll
talk about this there, okay?

28:52.456 --> 28:55.425
So, what's up with Riley?
She hasn't been herself lately.

28:55.459 --> 28:56.560
I don't know.

28:56.594 --> 28:57.895
Might have
something to do with

28:57.929 --> 28:58.896
her hubby getting
out of the clink.

28:58.930 --> 29:00.898
The clink? Really?

29:00.932 --> 29:01.899
Dude, she's a badass.

29:01.933 --> 29:03.801
[ Laughs ]
Ladies.

29:03.835 --> 29:06.503
[ Clears throat ] One of y'all's
gonna have to take my client.

29:06.537 --> 29:08.138
Why? You got a case
of the sniffles again?

29:08.173 --> 29:09.339
[ Chuckles ]

29:09.373 --> 29:11.075
Uh, who is it?

29:11.109 --> 29:13.077
- Quick draw McGraw.
- Ooh, yeah, I'll take him.

29:13.111 --> 29:15.679
Yeah, well, it's not like Selena
gave me a chance to answer,

29:15.714 --> 29:17.181
but I already have
a client.

29:17.215 --> 29:18.816
You can't even handle
"three jabs, you're out"?

29:18.850 --> 29:21.018
Girl, your indecent proposal
messed you up good.

29:21.052 --> 29:22.485
Wow.

29:22.520 --> 29:25.122
Hey.

29:25.156 --> 29:26.757
Hey.

29:26.791 --> 29:29.326
So, I've got a client
who might think

29:29.360 --> 29:31.862
that there's something more
going on between us.

29:31.896 --> 29:32.821
Is there?

29:32.941 --> 29:33.791
Definitely not.

29:33.911 --> 29:35.345
Is it Lisa?
You want me to talk to her?

29:35.465 --> 29:39.436
No, she's harmless. I just...
Don't know how to handle it.

29:39.470 --> 29:42.439
You can start
by giving that watch back.

29:42.473 --> 29:45.642
Look, I see things, Derek.
I see a lot of things.

29:45.676 --> 29:47.778
And I know that it is hard
to tell the difference between

29:47.812 --> 29:50.166
a happy ending
and a happily ever after.

29:50.286 --> 29:51.436
But you need to
make sure she knows

29:51.556 --> 29:54.852
that what we do around here, it is
only a fantasy. None of it's real.

29:54.886 --> 29:56.686
And if you need me to walk in
there and tell her, I will.

29:56.721 --> 29:58.889
I got it. Thanks.

29:58.923 --> 30:00.457
Okay, well...

30:00.491 --> 30:02.659
If she still doesn't get it,
she has to go.

30:02.693 --> 30:04.728
No wild cards on the list.

30:04.763 --> 30:06.764
[ Sighs ]

30:09.600 --> 30:11.401
Love that guy.

30:11.435 --> 30:12.836
[ Salsa music playing ]

30:12.871 --> 30:14.471
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:14.505 --> 30:18.075
Thank you.
This is very romantic.

30:18.109 --> 30:20.343
Barbecue's
never looked sexier.

30:20.378 --> 30:22.712
Mmm. This is good.

30:22.747 --> 30:25.149
Mmm. You got a little sauce
on your face.

30:25.183 --> 30:26.549
[ Laughs ]

30:26.584 --> 30:27.985
[ Chuckles ]

30:28.019 --> 30:29.186
Oh, thanks.

30:29.220 --> 30:30.821
So, Evan Parks,

30:30.855 --> 30:33.023
you bring
all your ladies here?

30:33.057 --> 30:34.491
Oh, well, if by ladies,

30:34.525 --> 30:37.161
you mean my buddies
from the rodeo, then yeah.

30:37.195 --> 30:38.996
Come on.

30:39.030 --> 30:40.697
You're handsome.
You're smart. You're funny.

30:40.731 --> 30:43.366
You have amazing taste in ribs
served from a truck.

30:43.401 --> 30:44.567
Thank you.

30:44.602 --> 30:45.568
Why are you single?

30:45.603 --> 30:47.504
Here we go.

30:47.538 --> 30:49.106
Yep, here we go.

30:49.140 --> 30:51.574
Uh,
I just haven't had time.

30:51.609 --> 30:54.778
My brother,
he deserted his family,

30:54.813 --> 30:58.015
and so...
I was looking after them.

30:58.049 --> 30:59.416
Filling
the "man in the house" role?

30:59.450 --> 31:01.051
Yeah. Yeah, I guess.

31:01.085 --> 31:03.053
I mean, they've been in my life
for a long time.

31:03.087 --> 31:04.454
I just
wanted to make sure

31:04.488 --> 31:07.691
my sister-in-law felt like
she had some support.

31:07.725 --> 31:09.693
It's just...
It's tough seeing my brother

31:09.727 --> 31:11.094
treat her the way he does.

31:11.129 --> 31:13.197
You know,
she deserves so much better.

31:13.231 --> 31:14.531
Someone like you?

31:14.565 --> 31:18.902
You really fell for her,
huh?

31:18.937 --> 31:22.239
I came close.
But I moved on.

31:22.273 --> 31:23.640
Wow. [ Laughs ]

31:23.674 --> 31:25.075
I knew you were hiding
some dark secrets.

31:25.109 --> 31:26.543
Oh, yeah?
How did you know?

31:26.577 --> 31:28.611
'Cause you should have been
all over me.

31:28.646 --> 31:31.715
I'm looking for someone with
a little more self-confidence.

31:31.749 --> 31:33.817
I think you might be
wasting my time.

31:33.852 --> 31:35.618
- Oh, yeah? How's that?
- Mm-hmm.

31:35.653 --> 31:37.454
I'm not sure why
you're over there talking

31:37.488 --> 31:40.390
when you could be
over here kissing.

31:40.424 --> 31:41.825
Oh, you want to kiss me?

31:41.860 --> 31:43.260
Maybe.

31:43.294 --> 31:44.661
I might be waiting for

31:44.695 --> 31:48.265
someone a little more
self-confident.

31:53.771 --> 31:55.138
Told you
this place was good.

31:55.173 --> 31:57.941
I'm still deciding.

31:57.976 --> 31:59.676
[ Chuckles ]

31:59.710 --> 32:03.513
I'm glad you're both here.

32:03.547 --> 32:05.949
Kyle just got out of jail.

32:05.984 --> 32:07.850
How has that been going
since he's back home?

32:07.970 --> 32:10.006
Um, he hasn't really
been staying at home.

32:10.126 --> 32:12.400
I left my wife.

32:12.657 --> 32:14.692
And I left my kids.

32:14.726 --> 32:16.026
And I know that...

32:16.060 --> 32:19.062
I know that this
is gonna take some time.

32:19.097 --> 32:20.731
Why did you leave?

32:20.765 --> 32:22.800
Had a drug problem.

32:22.834 --> 32:24.101
Are you still using?

32:24.135 --> 32:26.203
No, I've been clean
six months.

32:26.237 --> 32:27.938
That's good.

32:27.973 --> 32:32.209
Did you ever think
the drugs or your leaving

32:32.243 --> 32:33.911
were an escape
for something?

32:33.945 --> 32:35.445
Yeah.

32:35.480 --> 32:36.814
Any idea what?

32:36.848 --> 32:38.616
The truth.

32:38.650 --> 32:40.150
You know,
I was playing ball in college.

32:40.184 --> 32:45.589
There were a lot of expectations
for me to go pro.

32:45.624 --> 32:46.991
And then
I blew out my knee, and...

32:47.025 --> 32:48.659
and all that went away.

32:50.595 --> 32:54.765
I started taking pills
to numb the pain, and...

32:54.799 --> 32:56.767
and over time,

32:56.801 --> 33:00.103
I just started taking them
to numb everything.

33:00.138 --> 33:02.940
I'd look at my wife,
and I would think that...

33:02.974 --> 33:06.010
I would think that she should be
looking at something better.

33:07.979 --> 33:11.949
And I left.

33:11.983 --> 33:14.785
I was selfish.

33:19.190 --> 33:20.791
And now you're back.

33:20.825 --> 33:23.661
Yeah. I'm back.

33:23.695 --> 33:26.096
And what do you want?

33:26.130 --> 33:28.933
A second chance.

33:28.967 --> 33:32.536
I want to move
back into my house,

33:32.571 --> 33:34.371
be with my wife
and my two children.

33:34.405 --> 33:36.440
I slept with someone.

33:36.474 --> 33:39.009
[ Grace Potter & The Nocturnals'
"One Heart Missing" plays ]

33:48.920 --> 33:53.123
♪ My lonely heart
was made for two ♪

33:53.157 --> 33:57.962
[ Sobs ] ♪ it beats too
slowly without you ♪

33:57.996 --> 34:02.566
♪ you want to know
what we can be ♪

34:02.601 --> 34:04.001
♪ but you won't
give your love to me ♪

34:04.035 --> 34:06.837
Are you
gonna say anything?

34:06.871 --> 34:09.473
♪ Oh ♪

34:09.507 --> 34:14.411
♪ I'm calling your name,
but you won't listen ♪

34:14.445 --> 34:17.547
♪ oh ♪

34:17.581 --> 34:19.181
♪ if love is made for two ♪

34:19.217 --> 34:20.851
It wasn't Evan.

34:20.885 --> 34:23.887
♪ Then there's one ♪

34:23.922 --> 34:26.556
♪ heart ♪

34:26.591 --> 34:31.393
♪ missing ♪

34:31.429 --> 34:32.529
♪ one ♪

34:35.474 --> 34:38.442
[ Salsa music playing ]

34:38.476 --> 34:39.844
So, what about you?

34:39.878 --> 34:42.246
What about me?

34:42.280 --> 34:46.250
Well, you're pretty,
you're funny, you're smart,

34:46.284 --> 34:49.687
and that self-confident thing
is a little bit of a turn-on.

34:49.721 --> 34:50.755
Why are you single?

34:50.789 --> 34:54.891
[ Chuckles ]
Why am I single?

34:54.926 --> 34:57.728
Yeah. I guess I've been too busy

34:57.763 --> 35:00.297
trying to climb out
from under a heavy past.

35:00.331 --> 35:02.366
What?
From your Uncle?

35:02.401 --> 35:07.070
He started dealing drugs
to help my mom raise us,

35:07.105 --> 35:09.907
and he ran
with the wrong guys.

35:09.941 --> 35:13.110
And one day,

35:13.144 --> 35:15.446
he had me and my brothers
out playing soccer,

35:15.480 --> 35:19.049
and... a car drove by.

35:19.083 --> 35:20.885
The car slowed down,

35:20.919 --> 35:24.522
and I heard,
"pop, pop, pop."

35:26.625 --> 35:29.794
I watched him
die in front of me,

35:29.828 --> 35:32.797
and I knew right then and there
that I wanted to be a cop

35:32.831 --> 35:35.933
and that I wanted to get
far away from that place.

35:38.102 --> 35:41.505
Sorry you asked?

35:41.540 --> 35:43.373
Not at all.

35:49.080 --> 35:55.453
Georgia Cummings,
I'd like a whiskey, neat.

35:55.487 --> 35:56.921
I see you know my name,

35:56.955 --> 35:58.622
but we haven't been
introduced.

35:58.657 --> 36:00.057
Greg Carlyle.

36:00.091 --> 36:01.759
I know who you are,

36:01.793 --> 36:03.794
and there's a reason
we haven't met.

36:03.829 --> 36:07.030
So I suggest you get your butt
off that barstool.

36:07.065 --> 36:09.567
Go get your drink
somewhere else. We're closed.

36:09.601 --> 36:11.068
[ Chuckles ]

36:11.102 --> 36:14.572
That is just terrible manners
for a barkeep.

36:14.606 --> 36:17.475
It's probably a good thing
that you're selling the parlor.

36:17.509 --> 36:19.076
And I'd like to make
an offer.

36:19.110 --> 36:20.478
I already got a buyer.

36:20.512 --> 36:21.979
I'd like
to raise the offer

36:22.013 --> 36:25.215
$200,000 from what that
little dove is offering you.

36:25.249 --> 36:27.618
I have all the low-end
clientele in Texas.

36:27.652 --> 36:29.820
Now I'm after
all the high-end.

36:29.855 --> 36:32.155
I told you.

36:32.190 --> 36:35.158
I already got a buyer.

36:35.193 --> 36:36.794
Oh,
that just seems like

36:36.828 --> 36:40.230
a really bad
business decision to me.

36:40.264 --> 36:42.232
I bet
your man wouldn't mind

36:42.266 --> 36:45.636
his wifey
having an extra 200 grand.

36:45.670 --> 36:47.605
Oh, I get it.

36:47.639 --> 36:49.607
You are keeping this dirty,
little secret

36:49.641 --> 36:51.008
all to yourself.

36:51.042 --> 36:52.643
Well, didn't anyone
ever tell you

36:52.677 --> 36:54.277
you can't bury past sins?

36:54.312 --> 36:57.080
I'm not afraid
to bury more than that.

36:57.115 --> 37:01.151
You come back here again,
you're gonna find that out.

37:01.185 --> 37:04.187
I hope
you don't regret it.

37:10.461 --> 37:12.696
[ Moans ]

37:12.731 --> 37:14.698
I just can't seem

37:14.733 --> 37:19.136
to get enough of those
strong hands of yours.

37:19.170 --> 37:20.871
Lisa, we need to talk.

37:22.841 --> 37:26.644
Something tells me
you're not about to invite me

37:26.678 --> 37:30.848
on a romantic weekend
to South Padre Island.

37:30.882 --> 37:32.683
I am sorry,
but you pay me for an hour

37:32.717 --> 37:34.117
to make you feel good.

37:34.152 --> 37:37.187
Nothing more,
nothing less.

37:37.221 --> 37:42.626
[ Voice breaking ] I know.
I get carried away.

37:42.661 --> 37:43.994
[ Sighs ]

37:44.029 --> 37:48.999
The divorce
is just making me so sad.

37:49.034 --> 37:52.036
I was only looking
for a distraction.

37:52.070 --> 37:53.904
I know.

37:53.939 --> 37:57.340
[ Sighs ]
Don't cry, please.

37:57.375 --> 37:59.176
I wasn't trying
to be harsh.

37:59.210 --> 38:00.210
[ Sniffles ]

38:00.244 --> 38:02.646
Hey.

38:02.681 --> 38:04.848
I mean, if we'd met
under different circumstances,

38:04.883 --> 38:06.850
I'm sure we'd be great.

38:09.220 --> 38:10.588
You're just saying that.

38:10.622 --> 38:12.422
No. I'm not.

38:12.457 --> 38:14.391
Will you
accept the watch?

38:15.460 --> 38:17.761
My ex bought one

38:17.796 --> 38:20.263
for his secretary
that he was sleeping with.

38:20.298 --> 38:27.270
I know it's revenge-y
and childish, but...

38:27.305 --> 38:28.405
Thanks.

38:30.475 --> 38:33.844
Do you mind if we finish?

38:33.878 --> 38:36.080
No, of course not.

38:38.449 --> 38:40.050
So...

38:40.085 --> 38:44.888
if we had met under
different circumstances,

38:44.923 --> 38:50.427
where would we be
and what would you be wearing?

38:50.461 --> 38:52.630
[ Crickets chirping ]

38:55.299 --> 38:56.700
Hey.

38:56.735 --> 38:59.703
[ Sighs ]

38:59.738 --> 39:01.271
Thought we could
make these together.

39:01.305 --> 39:04.108
I'd like that.

39:04.142 --> 39:05.542
You tell Kyle?

39:05.576 --> 39:07.611
Parts.
And?

39:07.646 --> 39:09.446
He doesn't even
know everything

39:09.480 --> 39:10.881
'cause
he can't know everything.

39:10.915 --> 39:12.783
Well, maybe he shouldn't
have left.

39:12.817 --> 39:16.219
Sorry.
I'm being protective.

39:16.254 --> 39:18.388
No, it's fine.

39:18.422 --> 39:20.390
We all know
he shouldn't have left,

39:20.424 --> 39:22.793
but now he's back,

39:22.827 --> 39:24.227
and he's gonna
try to convince me

39:24.262 --> 39:26.263
that our family
is worth fighting for.

39:26.297 --> 39:28.999
- What will you do?
- I don't know.

39:29.034 --> 39:31.835
I mean, I've got two babies.
My bills are piling up.

39:31.870 --> 39:36.540
And the way I see it,
I am the best our family's got.

39:38.509 --> 39:41.311
Just promise me
no more secrets,

39:41.345 --> 39:43.613
'cause we're in this
to the bitter end, you and me.

39:43.648 --> 39:46.050
Promise.

39:49.487 --> 39:51.855
[ Sighs ]
Lacey, did you know

39:51.890 --> 39:54.692
that the traditional
seventh wedding-anniversary gift

39:54.726 --> 39:57.961
is... copper?

39:57.996 --> 40:00.197
[ Laughs ]
No, it is not.

40:00.231 --> 40:01.464
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

40:01.499 --> 40:03.300
Just to make things better,
it's copper.

40:03.334 --> 40:06.203
Well, Kyle sure got him
some copper, didn't he?

40:06.237 --> 40:08.038
Oh, he got a truckload.
[ Laughs ]

40:08.073 --> 40:10.674
Ohh.

40:10.709 --> 40:12.776
Come on.
Let's go make some pickles.

40:12.811 --> 40:14.111
Okay.

40:14.145 --> 40:17.181
Okay.

40:23.387 --> 40:25.189
Mommy?

40:25.223 --> 40:27.224
Yeah? When's mee maw
coming home?

40:27.258 --> 40:30.060
Oh, um, soon, baby.

40:30.095 --> 40:31.461
Real soon.

40:31.495 --> 40:33.864
Why isn't daddy
staying with us?

40:33.898 --> 40:37.400
Uh, because your daddy and I
need a little bit of time, okay?

40:37.435 --> 40:39.536
But he's gonna come
and take you both

40:39.570 --> 40:41.105
to school
tomorrow morning, right?

40:43.274 --> 40:46.476
Hey, you know what?
It's gonna be okay.

40:46.510 --> 40:48.245
Everything
is gonna be okay.

40:48.279 --> 40:50.881
Your mee maw's gonna be okay,
your daddy's gonna be okay,

40:50.915 --> 40:52.515
and, well, me,

40:52.550 --> 40:54.718
you're stuck with me
'cause I'm not going anywhere.

40:56.621 --> 41:04.621
♪ Why should I feel
discouraged? ♪

41:07.265 --> 41:15.265
♪ why should the shadows come? ♪

41:16.274 --> 41:24.274
♪ why should my heart
feel lonely? ♪

41:25.483 --> 41:28.685
♪ when all is heaven and home ♪

41:28.719 --> 41:32.689
Riley: Hey.

41:32.723 --> 41:36.293
Hey.

41:36.327 --> 41:40.197
Are you gonna talk to me
about this?

41:40.231 --> 41:42.099
Not right now.

41:42.133 --> 41:45.735
♪ When Jesus is my portion ♪

41:45.770 --> 41:47.938
Hey.

41:47.972 --> 41:51.041
You want to sit down with me
for a while?

41:51.075 --> 41:54.044
♪ A constant friend ♪

41:54.078 --> 41:56.680
- Yeah.
♪ - is He ♪

41:58.616 --> 42:06.616
♪ His eye is on the sparrow ♪

42:07.458 --> 42:14.431
♪ and I know He watches me ♪

42:14.551 --> 42:16.677
